social_posts.post_text: Thank you for your resilience, Jade.

#guyfieri #dinersdriveinsanddives #flavortown #guysbigbite #foodnetwork #why ?  I like Dave. Dave gets fun yet challenging tattoos. Dave doesn’t take things too seriously. Dave is cool. Please don’t ask me for portraits, because I don’t actually know what I’m doing. #chances #risk
Drawn on chain and morning star filler
That last tattoo I did in 2022 was one of my closest friends. Perfectly fitting in my opinion. Lucifer son of the morning, I’m going to chase you out of Earth.

Happy New Year everyone! I hope you’re feeling a sense of renewal today. I’m using this rare photo of myself in hopes Instxgrxm’s algorithm gets this message spread wide. I think the machine’s gears preferred lubricant is narcissism. Thank you to everyone that’s supported my work this past year, the years before and especially the years to come. There aren’t words that I know that accurately express my gratitude. To anyone I’ve made proud, to anyone I’ve disappointed,  I’m indebted to you for making life a continuous learning process. Every passing day has a lesson embedded to keep me on my toes. Reminding me to cherish the things that may get blurred by the speed of life. And even when I think I have it all figured out, moments have a way to humble me and remind me that I really don’t and I never will. Change is good. Adaptation is constant and feeling out of your comfort zone can be healthy. This all being said, after 19 years, this will most likely be my last year living in NYC. More details will come at a later time. Link in my bio if you want a tattoo in the meantime. Thanks for listening. 😘
